"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-team-gb-medal-target-2024-olympics-b1169421.html\", \"text\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies. Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search. See our privacy policy for more information.  Sport|Olympics  Team GBhave been set a medal target of between 50 and 70 at the upcomingOlympic Gamesin Paris.  Great Britainfinished fourth in the medal table at the last Games in Tokyo three years ago with 64 medals in total, just down on the 67 they won in Rio de Janeiro where they finished runner-up to the United States.  UK Sporthave set the target of 50 to 70 medals for the Olympics and 100 to 140 for theParalympics, with the aim of a top-five finish in the medal table in both Games.  Team GBhas finished in the top five of the Olympics for each Games since Beijing in 2008.  UK Sportchair DameKatherine Graingersaid: \\\"Paris offers the hugely exciting prospect of our brilliant British athletes competing on our doorstep.  \\\"It's also the first Games on a European time zone since London 2012, and I have no doubt that the British public will seize the moment to unite and cheer our incredible athletes to victory.\\\"  MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal 